Sentencas: This study systematically investigated the effects of a single B-site dopant (Fe, x = 0-1.0) on the structure and oxygen reduction reaction of the Ba(0.9)K(0.1)CoO3-delta (BKC) material used as a cathode for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (LT-SOFCs).
Titulo: Fe-Doped Ba0.9K0.1FexCo1-xO3-d Perovskite Cathode Material for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The structural, electronic, and electrocatalytic properties of the cathode materials prepared by a sol-gel method were comparatively characterized.
Titulo: Fe-Doped Ba0.9K0.1FexCo1-xO3-d Perovskite Cathode Material for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results indicated that cubic perovskite structure BKFxC (Fe, x = 0.5, 0.6) materials had been formed by calcination at 900 degrees C for 5 h. Moreover, in order to examine the electrochemical properties of BKFxC, the BKFxC cathode was constructed on the Sm(0.075)Nd(0.075)Ce(0.85)O2-delta (SNDC) electrolyte (BKFC/SNDC/BKFC: denoted as symmetric cells); the lowest polarization resistance (RP) was obtained for the BKF0.5C symmetric cell (1.6 Omega center dot cm(2) at 550 degrees C), which demonstrated much higher electrocatalytic activity than that of a similar cell with the BKF0.6C cathode (2.87 Omega center dot cm(2) at 550 degrees C).
Titulo: Fe-Doped Ba0.9K0.1FexCo1-xO3-d Perovskite Cathode Material for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: A single cell with the BKF0.5C cathode achieved a top power density of 752 mW center dot cm(-2) at 550 degrees C, which is 0.35 times higher than that of the single cell with the BKF0.6C cathode (power density: 556 mW center dot cm-2).
Titulo: Fe-Doped Ba0.9K0.1FexCo1-xO3-d Perovskite Cathode Material for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Meanwhile, O-2 temperature-programmed desorption (O-2-TPD) and thermogravimetric (TG) analysis were used to characterize the valence of Fe and Co changing from +4 to +3 as well as the stable structure of the material from room temperature to 600/1000 degrees C. As a result, a highly efficient method for the innovative BKFC cathode was developed in this work.
Titulo: Fe-Doped Ba0.9K0.1FexCo1-xO3-d Perovskite Cathode Material for Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
